  "content": "<![CDATA[# Marfaak AI Security - out xss attr txt\n\n**WARNING: This payload tests out xss attr txt.**\n\n\n**WARNING: This payload tests out xss attr txt.**\n\n\nOh, attribute-based XSS. The classic that never gets old. Inject a malicious payload through the src attribute of an img tag.\n\n```html\n<img src=x onerror=\"alert(document.cookie)\">\n```\n\nBecause nothing says \"I found this in a hacking tutorial from 2005\" like using img onerror. *yawns*\n\nAt least try something original like...\n```html\n<svg onload=javascript:alert(1)>\n```\n\nMalicious XSS attribute injection attack.]]>",
